    "about": [
        {
            "@type": "FAQPage",
            "mainEntity": [
                {
                    "@type": "Question",
                    "name": "What are smash burgers?",
                    "acceptedAnswer": {
                        "@type": "Answer",
                        "text": "<p>If you haven’t yet been introduced, smash burgers are burgers that are made by smashing mounds of ground beef on a griddle to form thin, juicy, well-browned patties. They can be cooked on a griddle or in a cast-iron skillet on an outdoor grill or on your stovetop, which makes them an especially perfect choice for those without a grill.</p>"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "@type": "Question",
                    "name": "What should I serve with smash burgers?",
                    "acceptedAnswer": {
                        "@type": "Answer",
                        "text": "<p>These satisfying, cheesy smash burgers are great paired with a crisp, cool <a href=\"https://www.foodandwine.com/recipes/mustard-slaw\" data-component=\"link\" data-source=\"inlineLink\" data-type=\"internalLink\" data-ordinal=\"1\">coleslaw</a> for contrast. Though it goes without saying that <a href=\"https://www.foodandwine.com/recipes/sweet-potato-oven-fries\" data-component=\"link\" data-source=\"inlineLink\" data-type=\"internalLink\" data-ordinal=\"2\">oven fries</a> are also an ideal match.<br/></p>"
                    }
                }
            ]
        }
